The paper focuses on the task of goal-oriented visual dialogue, which involves generating a series of questions about an image with a single objective. This task involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques, as well as reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) methods. Additionally, the paper proposes an end-to-end system that combines these techniques, which could also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO) since it involves creating an agent that can interact with its environment.
